==English==

===Pronunciation===
'''psy*cho'''
* [[IPA]]: /ˈsaɪkoʊ/
* [[SAMPA]]: /"saIkoU/
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪkəʊ|-aɪkəʊ]]

===Etymology===
Prefix ''[[psycho-]]'', as an abbreviation for ''psychotic'' or ''psychopath''.

===Adjective===
'''psycho'''

# {{colloquial}}: Psychotic, or otherwise [[insane]].

====Translations====
* [[Interlingua]]: [[psychotic]], [[psychopathic]]
* Portuguese: [[psicótico]] {{m}}, [[psicopático]] {{m}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|pejorative|slang}} A [[person]] who is [[psychotic]] or otherwise [[insane]].
#: ''The loony bin up on the hill is full of '''psychos'''.''
# {{context|pejorative|slang}} A [[person]] who acts in a [[bizarre]] or [[dangerous]] manner.
#: ''She complained that he was a '''psycho''' for driving at such a high speed in heavy traffic.''

====Synonyms====
* (''pejorative for a pyschotic or otherwise insane person''): [[freak]], [[loony]], [[nutcase]], [[wacko]]
* (''pejorative for a person acting in a bizarre or dangerous manner''): [[creep]], [[freak]], [[loose cannon]], [[weirdo]]

